{{Italic title}} '''''Order''''' (subtitled "A Journal on the Theory of Ordered Sets and its Applications") is a quarterly [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] on [[order theory]] and its applications, published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]]. It was founded in 1984 by [[University of Calgary]] mathematics professor [[Ivan Rival]];<ref>{{citation|title=Obituary: Ivan Rival|first=Dwight|last=Duffus|journal=Order|volume=20|issue=3|pages=173–183|year=2003|doi=10.1023/B:ORDE.0000026602.94442.32}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Ivan Rival 1947–2002|first=Bob|last=Quackenbush|journal=[[Algebra Universalis]]|volume=53|year=2005|pages=141–142|doi=10.1007/s00012-005-1000-y|url=http://www.ivanrival.com/docs/ir_obituary_au.pdf}}.</ref> as of 2010, its editor in chief is [[Dwight Duffus]], the Goodrich C. White Professor of Mathematics & Computer Science at [[Emory University]] and a former student of Rival's.<ref name="springer">[https://www.springer.com/mathematics/geometry/journal/11083 Publisher web site], retrieved 2010-09-10.</ref>
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the 2009 [[impact factor]] of ''Order'' is 0.408, placing it in the fourth quartile of ranked mathematics journals.<ref>[[Journal Citation Reports]], retrieved 2010-09-10.</ref>
